    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - DISASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the lift tool and slide the countershafts apart (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302355">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302355" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302355" filename="../figg13/g1302355.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Mainshaft &#38; Countershaft Disassembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft snap ring and 1st-reverse shift collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302356">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302356" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302356" filename="../figg13/g1302356.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Remove Mainshaft Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses to help protect your eyes against flying parts.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st and 2nd speed gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302357">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302357" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302357" filename="../figg13/g1302357.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Remove 1st &#38; 2nd Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed clutch collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302358">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302358" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302358" filename="../figg13/g1302358.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Remove 2nd - 3rd Speed Clutch Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 3rd and 4th speed gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302359">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302359" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302359" filename="../figg13/g1302359.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Remove 3rd &#38; 4th Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4th-5th speed shift collar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302360">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302360" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302360" filename="../figg13/g1302360.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Remove 4th - 5th Speed Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Notice that the fork slot on the 4th-5th speed shift collar (right,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302361">Figure 61</hotlnk>) is wider than the fork slot on the other collars in this
                unit.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302361" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302361" filename="../figg13/g1302361.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Note Fork Slot on 4th - 5th Speed Shift Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
